<paragraph blockId="29.[160,1155,1560,1690]" box="[160,262,1560,1586]" pageId="29" pageNumber="294">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[160,262,1560,1586]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="294">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[160,1155,1560,1690]" pageId="29" pageNumber="294">
This species is distinguished from similar ones like 
<taxonomicName authority="(Deshayes, 1857)" baseAuthorityName="Deshayes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[750,1044,1595,1620]" class="Ulvophyceae" family="Cladophoraceae" genus="Cladophora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cladophorales" pageId="29" pageNumber="294" phylum="Chlorophyta" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[750,843,1595,1620]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="294">C. viridis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Deshayes GP" box="[858,1036,1595,1620]" pageId="29" pageNumber="294" pagination="137 - 143" refId="ref19108" refString="Deshayes GP. 1857. Note sur differents Mollusques de la Guadeloupe, envoyes par M. Schramm. J Conchyliol. 6: 137 - 143." type="journal article" year="1857">Deshayes, 1857</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
(formerly 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Deshayes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[160,377,1630,1655]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hermaeidae" genus="Polybranchia" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="29" pageNumber="294" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[160,377,1630,1655]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="294">Polybranchia viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) by the presence of a ramified digestive gland in the cerata (see 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Deshayes" baseAuthorityYear="1857" box="[160,366,1665,1690]" class="Gastropoda" family="Hermaeidae" genus="Poybranchia" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="29" pageNumber="294" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis box="[160,366,1665,1690]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="294">Poybranchia viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation author="Rudman W" box="[402,558,1665,1690]" pageId="29" pageNumber="294" refId="ref22164" refString="Rudman W 2021. Sea Slug Forum. Sydney: Australian Museum. Accessed 2021 May 22. http: // www. seaslugforum. net / factsheet / tyloperv" type="journal volume" year="2021">Rudman 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
